{
  "video_id": "E4Ey_57IYwc",
  "title": "What does equal pay mean for the economy? | CNBC Explains",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 0.0,
      "end_time": 3200.0,
      "text": "Did you know that for every one dollar earned by a man,"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 3200.0,
      "end_time": 5540.0,
      "text": "a woman earns  around 80 cents?"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 5540.0,
      "end_time": 7340.0,
      "text": "That’s a pretty big gap."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 7340.0,
      "end_time": 9800.0,
      "text": "So what would happen  to the economy"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 9800.0,
      "end_time": 10120.0,
      "text": "if it was one for one?"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 15300.0,
      "end_time": 16620.0,
      "text": "Together, we&#39;re stronger!"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 16620.0,
      "end_time": 19300.0,
      "text": "The MeToo movement  has put gender inequality"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 19300.0,
      "end_time": 22800.0,
      "text": "in the spotlight from London  all the way to Hollywood,"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 22800.0,
      "end_time": 26360.0,
      "text": "and a lot of that inequality comes in the form of cold hard cash."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 26360.0,
      "end_time": 29380.0,
      "text": "The gender pay gap is the  difference in median earnings"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 29380.0,
      "end_time": 31000.0,
      "text": "between a man and a woman."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 31000.0,
      "end_time": 33320.0,
      "text": "It’s expressed as a percentage  of men’s earnings."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 33320.0,
      "end_time": 36200.0,
      "text": "So if the gender pay gap  is 20%, that means"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 36200.0,
      "end_time": 39780.0,
      "text": "a woman earns 80 cents for every one dollar earned by a man."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 39780.0,
      "end_time": 42500.0,
      "text": "OK, so how big of a gap are we talking about?"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 42500.0,
      "end_time": 44360.0,
      "text": "Well, it ranges around the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 44360.0,
      "end_time": 48460.0,
      "text": "Korea, Estonia and Japan have  some of the biggest gender pay gaps,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 48460.0,
      "end_time": 52160.0,
      "text": "while Costa Rica, Luxembourg and Greece have the smallest gaps."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 52160.0,
      "end_time": 54580.0,
      "text": "So why do women  earn less than men?"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 54580.0,
      "end_time": 56680.0,
      "text": "There are a lot of  pieces to this puzzle."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 56680.0,
      "end_time": 59000.0,
      "text": "Let’s use some fictional characters here in the U.K."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 59000.0,
      "end_time": 60260.0,
      "text": "to try to put it together."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 60260.0,
      "end_time": 62100.0,
      "text": "Meet Sally and James."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 62100.0,
      "end_time": 64280.0,
      "text": "Let’s pretend they both start working"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 64280.0,
      "end_time": 66440.0,
      "text": "in full-time jobs  at the same age."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 66440.0,
      "end_time": 68160.0,
      "text": "Research from the  U.K. government shows"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 68160.0,
      "end_time": 70520.0,
      "text": "Sally is likely to work  in the caring, leisure"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 70520.0,
      "end_time": 71880.0,
      "text": "and service industries,"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 71880.0,
      "end_time": 74160.0,
      "text": "or in an administrative  or secretarial job."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 74380.0,
      "end_time": 77759.0,
      "text": "James, meanwhile, is more likely  to work in skilled trades"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 77760.0,
      "end_time": 80500.0,
      "text": "or as a process, plant  or machine operator."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 80500.0,
      "end_time": 82240.0,
      "text": "These differences  in occupations"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 82240.0,
      "end_time": 84520.0,
      "text": "account for a big  part of the pay gap."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 84520.0,
      "end_time": 86880.0,
      "text": "But there’s another  important factor, too."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 87500.0,
      "end_time": 89220.0,
      "text": "Yep, motherhood."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 89220.0,
      "end_time": 91500.0,
      "text": "Even though Sally and James  start out making about the"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 91500.0,
      "end_time": 93220.0,
      "text": "the same amount of  money, the pay gap"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 93220.0,
      "end_time": 96190.0,
      "text": "really starts to widen in their mid-30s and 40s."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 96190.0,
      "end_time": 99100.0,
      "text": "Sally might stop working  or start working part-time"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 99100.0,
      "end_time": 101160.0,
      "text": "for a while to  raise a family,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 101160.0,
      "end_time": 102920.0,
      "text": "and when she comes back to work full-time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 102920.0,
      "end_time": 106000.0,
      "text": "she earns a lot less than  her male counterparts."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 106000.0,
      "end_time": 108700.0,
      "text": "Not to mention, it’s estimated  women like Sally"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 108700.0,
      "end_time": 112420.0,
      "text": "account for 75% of the world’s total unpaid work,"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 112420.0,
      "end_time": 115500.0,
      "text": "including crucial tasks to  keep households running."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 117000.0,
      "end_time": 119400.0,
      "text": "One thing to note is that even after looking at"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 119400.0,
      "end_time": 121380.0,
      "text": "differences in occupations and work hours,"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 121380.0,
      "end_time": 125399.0,
      "text": "the U.K. government found  that 64% of the gender pay gap"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 125400.0,
      "end_time": 127440.0,
      "text": "couldn&#39;t be explained, and some see this as"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 127440.0,
      "end_time": 129960.0,
      "text": "evidence of discrimination  in the workplace."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 129960.00000000001,
      "end_time": 131440.0,
      "text": "But regardless of the causes of the"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 131440.0,
      "end_time": 134520.0,
      "text": "gender pay gap, most experts agree leveling it out"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 134520.0,
      "end_time": 136820.0,
      "text": "will have big-time  economic benefits."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 137580.0,
      "end_time": 139440.0,
      "text": "One study found that  equal pay would cut"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 139440.0,
      "end_time": 142140.0,
      "text": "the poverty rate of working women in half,"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 142140.0,
      "end_time": 145700.0,
      "text": "and produce an additional  income of around $512 billion"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 145700.0,
      "end_time": 147220.0,
      "text": "to the U.S. economy."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 147780.0,
      "end_time": 150000.0,
      "text": "Another report found that  if women in developing countries"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 150000.0,
      "end_time": 152400.0,
      "text": "were paid as  much as men,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 152400.0,
      "end_time": 154140.0,
      "text": "they could earn  an extra $2 trillion."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 154140.0,
      "end_time": 156459.0,
      "text": "That’s an 18%  bump in pay."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 157500.0,
      "end_time": 159460.0,
      "text": "Plus there are economic  bonuses just from"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 159460.0,
      "end_time": 161740.0,
      "text": "putting more women to work."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 161740.0,
      "end_time": 164780.0,
      "text": "In 2017, just under half  of working-age women"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 164780.0,
      "end_time": 166620.0,
      "text": "participated in  the labor market."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 166620.0,
      "end_time": 169220.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s compared to  75% of men."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 169220.0,
      "end_time": 172300.0,
      "text": "If as many women worked as men, the IMF estimates"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 172300.0,
      "end_time": 175400.0,
      "text": "GDP would increase by 5% in the U.S."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 175400.0,
      "end_time": 176299.0,
      "text": "9% in Japan"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 176300.0,
      "end_time": 178200.0,
      "text": "12% in the UAE"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 178200.0,
      "end_time": 180200.0,
      "text": "and 27% in India."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 180200.0,
      "end_time": 182600.0,
      "text": "The IMF also found  that bringing more women"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 182600.0,
      "end_time": 184540.0,
      "text": "into the boardroom  can directly boost"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 184540.0,
      "end_time": 186340.0,
      "text": "a company’s  bottom line."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 186340.0,
      "end_time": 189400.0,
      "text": "Some countries haven’t been able to ignore these numbers."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 189400.0,
      "end_time": 191700.0,
      "text": "As of 2017, the U.K.  mandated that companies"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 191700.0,
      "end_time": 193260.0,
      "text": "with more than  250 employees"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 193260.0,
      "end_time": 195480.0,
      "text": "report gender pay gaps in the workplace."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 195480.0,
      "end_time": 198220.0,
      "text": "This year, Iceland enacted  a first-of-its-kind law"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 198220.0,
      "end_time": 201200.0,
      "text": "that forces companies  to eliminate pay gaps."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 201200.0,
      "end_time": 203500.0,
      "text": "Some companies are creating  more flexible policies"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 203500.0,
      "end_time": 206360.0,
      "text": "for women who want to work full-time and have children,"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 206360.0,
      "end_time": 208520.0,
      "text": "and for men to take paternity leave."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 208520.0,
      "end_time": 211360.0,
      "text": "Agencies like the U.N. promote higher education"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 211360.0,
      "end_time": 214260.0,
      "text": "and skills training to bring more women into the workforce."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 214260.0,
      "end_time": 217190.0,
      "text": "These efforts look like  steps in the right direction."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 217200.0,
      "end_time": 219680.0,
      "text": "But research shows  it will still take 100 years"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 219680.0,
      "end_time": 221360.0,
      "text": "to close the  global gender gap."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 221360.0,
      "end_time": 223000.0,
      "text": "And for many people here,  closing the gap isn&#39;t"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 223000.0,
